==English==

===Etymology===
[[Cf.]] Latin ''addictio'' an [[adjudje|adjudging]]

===Noun===
#The state of being [[addict]]ed; [[devotion]];[[inclination]].
#A habit or practice that damages, jeopardizes or shortens one's life but when ceased causes trauma.
#A progressive, incurable, and mostly fatal illness.
#A patholgical relationship to mood altering experience that has life damaging consequences.
#:*His addiction was to courses vain. ''[[Shakespeare]]''.

===Translations==
